description:
Background
- Parallel implementation requires stable file boundaries to reserve.

Scope
- Create the module/file layout that other tasks will fill in.
- Add empty mod.rs files and minimal wiring so modules compile.

File scope (expected)
- src/csv/{input.rs,sep.rs,dialect.rs,parser.rs,records.rs,blank.rs,mod.rs}
- src/normalize/{trim.rs,headers.rs,mod.rs}
- src/format/{numbers.rs,ident_human.rs,ident_json.rs,mod.rs}
- src/alignment/{row_order.rs,key_parse.rs,key_join.rs,key_discovery.rs,shuffle.rs,mod.rs}
- src/numeric/{missing.rs,parse.rs,columns.rs,missingness.rs,no_numeric.rs,mod.rs}
- src/diff/{tolerance.rs,heap.rs,coverage.rs,order.rs,mod.rs}
- src/output/human/{header.rs,real_change.rs,no_real.rs,refusal.rs,mod.rs}
- src/output/{json.rs,mod.rs}
- src/refusal/{codes.rs,details.rs,process.rs,mod.rs}
- src/cli/{args.rs,delimiter.rs,exit.rs,mod.rs}
- src/orchestrator.rs (or src/pipeline.rs)

Considerations
- Keep files minimal; no behavior beyond placeholders.
- Prefer one responsibility per file to maximize parallelization.

Acceptance
- Project builds with empty stubs and predictable file paths for reservation.
